# Home server vs dev machines

**Never treat the current machine as the home server.** Dev machines (Windows PC, Mac, phone) are for Cursor, git, and local `pnpm dev` only.

| Host | Role |
|------|------|
| **Vercel** | Next.js app + dashboard (`https://clip-operator.vercel.app`) |
| **Home server** | SupoClip + TikTok publisher, 24/7 |
| **This machine** | Development only |

## Before changing production infra

1. Read `deploy/HOME-SERVER.md` and `deploy/home-server.env` (if present).
2. Use `deploy/remote.ps1` / `deploy/remote.sh` for SSH — do not run `install-windows-home-server.ps1` on a dev PC.
3. Do not use Cloudflare quick tunnels (`trycloudflare.com`).

## Connection (local Cursor)

SSH over Tailscale — see `deploy/ssh-config.example` and `deploy/home-server.env.example`.

## Connection (Cloud Cursor)

Cloud agents cannot reach private Tailscale IPs. Deploy via **git push → GitHub Actions self-hosted runner** on the home server (`.github/workflows/deploy-home-server.yml`).

## Publisher

Home server publisher polls **Vercel** (`CLIP_OPERATOR_URL=https://clip-operator.vercel.app`), not localhost. Heartbeats land in Supabase — both Vercel and local dev read the same status.

## Local dev on this PC (localhost:3000)

Daily workflow — tunnel home-server SupoClip, then Clip Operator:

```powershell
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File deploy/start-dev.ps1
```

Or: `deploy/dev-tunnel.ps1` (leave open) + `pnpm dev`.

| URL | What |
|-----|------|
| http://localhost:3000 | Clip Operator dashboard |
| http://localhost:3107 | SupoClip UI (tunneled from home server) |
| http://localhost:8000 | SupoClip API (tunneled) |

Production dashboard: https://clip-operator.vercel.app
